{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01NWoEdaV4NTDK5fXxRFPNG1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QzZjPuBnBJi3CfbVZqyG3X","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md","offset":100},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10749,"cache_read_input_tokens":28617,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":10749,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Em2XRw3Hi7aBBMc3mqbUYk","session_id":"d06dabce-ed3c-4abf-ad84-f2845532d39a","uuid":"cd7c8bd9-ec78-46d9-8cac-183a9a12cb07"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QzZjPuBnBJi3CfbVZqyG3X","type":"tool_result","content":"   100→**Decision:** Report static coverage and runtime coverage as separate numbers. No weighted combination.\n   101→\n   102→**Rationale (from research):**\n   103→- \"Static: 85%, Runtime: 42%\" tells you static analysis is mostly passing but telemetry isn't flowing — the problem is in instrumentation setup\n   104→- \"Combined: 68%\" hides that distinction\n   105→- Different problems, different fixes — combining them loses diagnostic value\n   106→\n   107→**Metric storage in state:**\n   108→\n   109→```typescript\n   110→interface ObservabilityCoverage {\n   111→  static: {\n   112→    coveragePercent: number;    // functions with logs / total functions\n   113→    errorHandlerCoverage: number; // error handlers with logs / total error handlers\n   114→    lastScanTimestamp: string;\n   115→  };\n   116→  runtime: {\n   117→    telemetryDetected: boolean;  // any telemetry appeared during test run\n   118→    modulesWithTelemetry: number;\n   119→    totalModules: number;\n   120→    coveragePercent: number;     // modules with telemetry / total modules\n   121→    lastValidationTimestamp: string;\n   122→  };\n   123→  targets: {\n   124→    staticTarget: number;   // default 80\n   125→    runtimeTarget: number;  // default 60 (lower — harder to achieve)\n   126→  };\n   127→}\n   128→```\n   129→\n   130→### Decision 3: Runtime Validation — Verification IS the Runtime Check\n   131→\n   132→**Decision:** Runtime observability validation happens DURING black-box verification, not as a separate step. Every user interaction with the software during verification must produce at least one log entry in the observability stack.\n   133→\n   134→**Rationale:**\n   135→- The verifier already runs commands via `docker exec` — each command IS a user interaction\n   136→- The observability stack is already running during verification\n   137→- If a `docker exec codeharness init` produces zero logs, that's both a functional concern AND an observability gap\n   138→- No separate \"runtime validation\" step needed — verification validates both functional correctness and observability simultaneously\n   139→\n   140→**Approach:**\n   141→1. Verifier runs `docker exec` command for an AC (existing)\n   142→2. After each command, verifier queries the observability backend for log events in the time window of that command\n   143→3. If zero log events appeared → add observability gap note to the AC proof section\n   144→4. Proof document includes both functional evidence AND observability evidence\n   145→5. A story with all ACs passing functionally but zero observability can still fail if the observability target isn't met\n   146→\n   147→**Verification prompt update:** The verify-prompt.ts template adds an instruction:\n   148→```\n   149→After each docker exec command, query the observability endpoint for log events\n   150→from the last 30 seconds. If zero events appeared, note this in the AC section as:\n   151→[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction.\n   152→```\n   153→\n   154→**Coverage from verification:**\n   155→- Runtime coverage = (ACs with at least one log event / total ACs verified) × 100\n   156→- This is more meaningful than module-level matching — it directly measures \"does user interaction produce logs?\"\n   157→- Reported alongside static coverage in audit results\n   158→\n   159→**Standalone runtime check (audit mode):**\n   160→For projects that want runtime validation outside of verification, `codeharness audit` can also:\n   161→1. Run `npm test` with OTLP enabled\n   162→2. Query observability backend for events during test window\n   163→3. Report module-level coverage: did each module emit any telemetry during tests?\n   164→This is the fallback for projects not yet going through full verification.\n   165→\n   166→### Decision 4: Audit Module — Coordinator Pattern\n   167→\n   168→**Decision:** Audit is a coordinator that calls existing modules + new observability module. Not a monolith.\n   169→\n   170→```typescript\n   171→// audit/index.ts\n   172→export function runAudit(projectDir: string): Result<AuditResult> {\n   173→  const observability = observabilityModule.analyze(projectDir);\n   174→  const testing = coverageModule.check(projectDir);\n   175→  const documentation = docHealth.scan(projectDir);\n   176→  const verification = verifyModule.getStatus(projectDir);\n   177→  const infrastructure = infraModule.validateDockerfile(projectDir);\n   178→\n   179→  return ok({\n   180→    dimensions: { observability, testing, documentation, verification, infrastructure },\n   181→    overallStatus: computeOverall(...),\n   182→    gapCount: countGaps(...),\n   183→  });\n   184→}\n   185→\n   186→export function generateFixStories(auditResult: AuditResult): Result<Story[]> {\n   187→  // Uses existing epic-generator pattern from onboard\n   188→}\n   189→```\n   190→\n   191→**`onboard` becomes alias:** Same action handler, different command name. Backward compatible.\n   192→\n   193→### Decision 5: Infrastructure Validation — Rules as Markdown\n   194→\n   195→**Decision:** Dockerfile rules stored in `patches/infra/dockerfile-rules.md`. Validator parses the Dockerfile and checks against rules. Rules are human-readable and editable.\n   196→\n   197→**Rules format:**\n   198→\n   199→```markdown\n   200→## Required Elements\n   201→\n   202→1. FROM statement must use a pinned version (not :latest)\n   203→2. Project binary must be installed and on PATH\n   204→3. Verification tools must be present: showboat, claude, curl, jq\n   205→4. No COPY of source directories (src/, lib/, test/)\n   206→5. Non-root user for runtime\n   207→6. Cache cleanup (apt, npm, pip)\n   208→\n   209→## Project-Type Specific\n   210→\n   211→### Node.js\n   212→- node and npm available\n   213→- Project installed via tarball (npm pack + npm install -g)\n   214→\n   215→### Python\n   216→- python and pip available\n   217→- Project installed via wheel or sdist\n   218→\n   219→### Plugin\n   220→- claude CLI available with ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\n   221→```\n   222→\n   223→**Validator approach:** Parse Dockerfile line by line. Check for required patterns. Report missing as gaps. Simple regex matching — no Docker build required for validation.\n   224→\n   225→### Decision 6: Module Structure\n   226→\n   227→```\n   228→src/modules/\n   229→├── observability/              # NEW\n   230→│   ├── index.ts                # analyze, validateRuntime, getCoverage\n   231→│   ├── analyzer.ts             # Runs Semgrep (or configured tool), parses output\n   232→│   ├── runtime-validator.ts    # Post-test telemetry check via ObservabilityBackend\n   233→│   ├── coverage.ts             # Computes and tracks coverage metrics\n   234→│   ├── types.ts                # AnalyzerResult, ObservabilityGap, ObservabilityCoverage\n   235→│   └── __tests__/\n   236→├── audit/                      # NEW — replaces onboard\n   237→│   ├── index.ts                # runAudit, generateFixStories\n   238→│   ├── dimensions.ts           # Per-dimension check functions\n   239→│   ├── report.ts               # Human-readable + JSON formatting\n   240→│   └── __tests__/\n   241→├── infra/                      # EXTENDED\n   242→│   ├── ...existing...\n   243→│   ├── dockerfile-validator.ts # NEW — rule-based Dockerfile checking\n   244→│   └── __tests__/\n   245→└── ...existing modules unchanged...\n   246→\n   247→patches/\n   248→├── observability/              # NEW — Semgrep rules\n   249→│   ├── catch-without-logging.yaml\n   250→│   ├── function-no-debug-log.yaml\n   251→│   └── error-path-no-log.yaml\n   252→├── infra/\n   253→│   ├── ...existing...\n   254→│   └── dockerfile-rules.md     # NEW\n   255→├── dev/\n   256→│   └── dev-enforcement.md      # UPDATED — add \"run Semgrep before commit\"\n   257→└── review/\n   258→    └── review-enforcement.md   # UPDATED — add \"check observability gaps\"\n   259→\n   260→commands/\n   261→├── audit.ts                    # NEW — codeharness audit [--fix] [--json]\n   262→├── onboard.ts                  # MODIFIED — becomes alias for audit\n   263→└── ...existing unchanged...\n   264→```\n   265→\n   266→### Decision 7: Semgrep Integration\n   267→\n   268→**Decision:** Semgrep is a dev dependency, not bundled. The observability module spawns `semgrep` as a subprocess.\n   269→\n   270→```typescript\n   271→// observability/analyzer.ts\n   272→function runSemgrep(projectDir: string, rulesDir: string): Result<AnalyzerResult> {\n   273→  const args = ['scan', '--config', rulesDir, '--json', projectDir];\n   274→  const result = execFileSync('semgrep', args, { ... });\n   275→  return parseResult(JSON.parse(result));\n   276→}\n   277→```\n   278→\n   279→**If Semgrep is not installed:** Audit reports \"static analysis skipped — install semgrep\" as a warning. Not a hard failure. Users who don't want static analysis can skip it.\n   280→\n   281→**Semgrep output → AnalyzerResult mapping:** Semgrep's JSON output includes file, line, rule_id, message, severity. Maps directly to our `ObservabilityGap` interface.\n   282→\n   283→## Implementation Patterns\n   284→\n   285→All patterns from overhaul architecture apply (Result<T>, module boundaries, atomic writes, <300 lines, index.ts exports). Additional:\n   286→\n   287→### Semgrep Rule Pattern\n   288→\n   289→Rules in `patches/observability/` follow Semgrep YAML format. Users can:\n   290→- Edit existing rules (change logging function names)\n   291→- Add rules (custom patterns for their framework)\n   292→- Disable rules (remove the file)\n   293→\n   294→### Audit Dimension Pattern\n   295→\n   296→Each dimension check follows the same signature:\n   297→\n   298→```typescript\n   299→function checkDimension(projectDir: string): Result<DimensionResult> {\n   300→  // ... check logic ...\n   301→  return ok({\n   302→    status: 'pass' | 'fail' | 'warn',\n   303→    metric: number | string,\n   304→    gaps: Gap[],\n   305→  });\n   306→}\n   307→```\n   308→\n   309→Audit coordinator calls all dimensions, collects results, formats report.\n   310→\n   311→## Validation\n   312→\n   313→### FR Coverage\n   314→\n   315→| FR | Module | Decision |\n   316→|----|--------|----------|\n   317→| FR1-5 | observability/ | Decision 1 (Semgrep), Decision 2 (separate metrics) |\n   318→| FR6-9 | observability/ | Decision 3 (module-level matching) |\n   319→| FR10-12 | observability/ | Decision 2 (separate metrics, enforcement via hooks) |\n   320→| FR13-21 | audit/ | Decision 4 (coordinator pattern) |\n   321→| FR22-25 | infra/ | Decision 5 (rules as markdown) |\n   322→| FR26-28 | patches/ | Decisions 1, 4 (Semgrep in review, audit in workflows) |\n   323→\n   324→### Gaps: None\n   325→\n   326→All 28 FRs covered. All 9 NFRs addressed by existing patterns (Result<T>, <300 lines, both backends, UX format).\n   327→\n   328→### Readiness: YES\n   329→\n   330→Implementation order:\n   331→1. Semgrep rules in `patches/observability/` (no code — just YAML)\n   332→2. `observability/analyzer.ts` (run Semgrep, parse output)\n   333→3. `observability/coverage.ts` (compute static coverage)\n   334→4. `audit/` module (coordinator, replaces onboard)\n   335→5. `infra/dockerfile-validator.ts` (rule-based checking)\n   336→6. `observability/runtime-validator.ts` (post-test telemetry check)\n   337→7. Update patches for dev/review workflows\n   338→8. `commands/audit.ts` (CLI command)\n   339→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Em2XRw3Hi7aBBMc3mqbUYk","session_id":"d06dabce-ed3c-4abf-ad84-f2845532d39a","uuid":"dc90b0cd-7e79-4790-8f2e-ea799812291a","timestamp":"2026-03-21T05:14:50.868Z"}
